%H A035096 <a href="/index/Pri#primes_AP">Index entries for sequences related to primes in arithmetic progressions</a>.
%F A035096 a(n) = (A035095(n)-1)/A000040(n). - _Zak Seidov_, Dec 27 2013
%e A035096 a(15)=6 because the 15th prime is 47, and the smallest k such that 47k+1 is prime is k=6, for which 47k+1=283.
%t A035096 Reap[Sow[1]; Do[p = Prime[n]; k = 2; While[! PrimeQ[k*p + 1], k = k + 2]; Sow[k], {n, 2, 10^4}]][[2, 1]] (* _Zak Seidov_, Jan 28 2012 *)
%t A035096 f[n_] := Block[{p = Prime@ n}, q = 1 + 2p; While[ !PrimeQ@ q, q += 2p]; (q - 1)/p]; f[1] = 1; Array[f, 88] (* _Robert G. Wilson v_, Dec 27 2014 *)
